description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Ward Clerk within the Mental Health and Learning Disabilities Directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to carry out reception duties in a polite and courteous manner, having an awareness of customer care needs. Exchange information with patients, relatives and staff whilst maintaining confidentiality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meet and greet patients and carers, responding to their needs as appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undertake a full range of clerical typing duties for the Nursing Team, utilizing appropriate IT systems in place, including the range of Microsoft packages and emails.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide confidential routine clerical / typing duties&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Admit and discharge on patient hospital IT systems – Welshpas. PIMS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist with developing and maintain efficient and effective systems to ensure the smooth running of the office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJayne BeerJob titleHead of AdministrationEmail addressjayne.beer@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number07773481025 / 01639 683216&lt;/p&gt;
